http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Karimnagar-to-get-new-JNNURM-buses/article13993345.ece

The long-cherished dream of city bus services to the people of Karimnagar will be fulfilled on Monday with the flagging off of Jawaharlal Nehru National Urban Renewable Mission (JNNURM) buses by Transport Minister Mahender Reddy at Circus Grounds in Karimnagar.Minister for Finance Etala Rajender, Karimnagar MP B. Vinod Kumar, legislator Gangula Kamalakar, MLC Naradasu Laxman Rao, ZP chairperson Tula Uma and others would also grace the function.The RTC would initial launch 16 JNNURM bus services on two routes viz Kothapalli to Jyothismathi Institute of Technology and Science (JITS) via Karimnagar and Bahupeta to Nagunuru via Karimnagar.The remaining buses would be operated in a phased manner in all other routes.It may be recalled that then Union government had sanctioned 70 buses under JNNURM scheme to Karimnagar district including 50 buses for Karimnagar and 20 buses for Ramagundam.It was also decided to construct a city bus depot at RTC workshop on Jagtial road in Karimnagar.